---
import HubLayout from "../../layouts/HubLayout.astro";
---

<HubLayout
  title="About | Project Avinoc"
  description="About the Project Avinoc site."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-wrap">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>About Project Avinoc</h1>
        <p>
          This site is a personal project that consolidates tools and resources for the games I play
          into a single, clean web experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container stack" style="max-width: 42rem;">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Each game section is self-contained with its own guides, tools, and data. The site is built
        with Astro for static content and React for interactive tools like the fleet builder.
        Everything is open source and deployed via GitHub Pages.
      </p>

      <h2>Source policy</h2>
      <p>
        StarSavior content is adapted from Bullet's published strategy spreadsheet and explicitly
        cites the original source. All content is committed as static files — no live spreadsheet
        dependencies.
      </p>

      <h2>Tech stack</h2>
      <p>
        Astro 6 with MDX for guides, React 19 for interactive tools, Tailwind CSS for the fleet
        builder, vanilla CSS for everything else, Pagefind for full-text search, and GitHub Pages
        for hosting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</HubLayout>
